# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers per path.
#
# Syntax: <pattern> <owner> [more owners...]
# Owners can be GitHub usernames (@user) or team slugs (@org/team).
# Last matching pattern wins, so put the catch-all first and refine below.
#
# !! Replace the @placeholder owners below with real GitHub handles before
# !! turning on branch protection that requires CODEOWNERS review. Until then,
# !! these rules are advisory — PRs won't be blocked on missing reviewers.

# Catch-all — every file needs at least this team's approval.
*                              @your-org/frontend-team

# Build, CI, and security-critical paths — extra eyes from platform/security.
/.github/                      @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops
/.github/workflows/            @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops
/.github/dependabot.yml        @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops
/.husky/                       @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops

# Build tooling and dependency surface.
/package.json                  @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops
/package-lock.json             @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops
/vite.config.ts                @your-org/frontend-team
/vitest.config.ts              @your-org/frontend-team
/tsconfig*.json                @your-org/frontend-team
/eslint.config.js              @your-org/frontend-team
/scripts/                      @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/devops

# Security-sensitive runtime surface — auth/session, persisted state, Sentry, HTTP.
/src/store/                    @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/security
/src/core/sentry/              @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/security
/src/core/http/                @your-org/frontend-team @your-org/security

# Process docs — keep aligned with how the team actually works.
/CONTRIBUTING.md               @your-org/frontend-team
/README.md                     @your-org/frontend-team
/audit.md                      @your-org/frontend-team
